claim.claim-text:
12. A hydrostatic gas bearing device for use in a vacuum environment, in which 
a guide shaft and a moving body moving along said guide shaft are provided in a vacuum chamber; 
said moving body is formed with an air pad for releasing gas fed from the outside into a gap between said moving body and said guide shaft; 
an atmospheric pressure groove, which recovers the gas released into said gap and discharges the recovered gas to the outside through a pipe, is provided around said air pad; and 
a pressure reducing groove, which recovers the gas having not been recovered by said atmospheric pressure groove and discharges the recovered gas to the outside through a pipe, is provided around said atmospheric pressure groove, characterized in that 
in a pipe for discharging the gas recovered through said atmospheric pressure groove to the outside, there is provided a pressure buffering chamber, in which the internal gas pressure thereof is a fixed pressure higher than the atmospheric pressure so that gas does not flow backward from the outside to said atmospheric pressure groove through said pipe.
